{"id":25144,"date":"2017-08-09T13:55:49","date_gmt":"2017-08-09T09:55:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25144"},"modified":"2023-08-11T09:58:40","modified_gmt":"2023-08-11T05:58:40","slug":"dua-nawm-waking-up","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/08\/09\/dua-nawm-waking-up\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet\u2019s supplication for sleep, waking up"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hudhayfah reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, laid down at night, he would place his hand under his cheek and then say, \u201c<strong>O Allah, in Your name I die and I live<\/strong>.\u201d When the Prophet would awaken, he would say, \u201c<strong>All praise is due to Allah, who has given us life after our death, and unto Him is the Resurrection.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5955<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p>Ibn al-Qayyim said, \u201cThe Prophet would sleep when it was called for sleep, upon his right side and remembering Allah until sleep overtook his eyes.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-\u1e6cibb al-Nabaw\u012b 1\/179<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062d\u064f\u0630\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0641\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0630\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0636\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064